# Poss.Win.Automation

**Dependencies:** keep NuGet package references in `PoE.csproj` (`Poss.Win.Automation.Core`, `.Input`, `.GlobalHotKeys`). Do not replace them with local project references.

**Usage questions:** when you need to know how the library works — APIs, key strings, enums, hotkey behavior — read the local source repo instead of inspecting NuGet packages or guessing:

`C:\Users\Latur\source\repos\Poss.Win.Automation`

| NuGet package | Read here for usage |
|---|---|
| `Poss.Win.Automation.Core` | `src/Poss.Win.Automation.Core/` |
| `Poss.Win.Automation.Input` | `src/Poss.Win.Automation.Input/` |
| `Poss.Win.Automation.GlobalHotKeys` | `src/Poss.Win.Automation.GlobalHotKeys/` |

Useful entry points:

- `VirtualKey`: `src/Poss.Win.Automation.Core/Common/Enums/VirtualKey.cs` (`ushort` underlying type)
- Key strings for `Send()` / hotkeys: `src/Poss.Win.Automation.Core/Common/Structs/KeyStroke.cs`
- Input: `src/Poss.Win.Automation.Input/Input/InputSimulator.cs`
- Hotkeys: `src/Poss.Win.Automation.GlobalHotKeys/GlobalHotKey/GlobalHotKeyManager.cs`

## Key name conventions (from KeyStroke)

Stored key strings must match what `KeyStroke.TryParse` accepts:

- Digits: `"1"`, `"2"`, … — not `"D1"`, `"D2"`
- Letters: `"A"`, `"B"`, …
- Modifiers / mouse: `"Ctrl"`, `"Shift"`, `"LButton"`, etc.
- Actions: `"1 Down"`, `"F5 Up"`, `"LButton Press"`

For `Enum.IsDefined(typeof(VirtualKey), value)`, pass `ushort` — not `int`.
